story.title: My Confidant - Episode 2
story.storyDescription: When Lucy hears a stranger break into her apartment, she texts her long-distance boyfriend, Brendan. Too bad there’s nothing he can do to save her…
story.creator: web-uploader

messages.text: Holy shit, Luce
That could have been you
Brendan, my best friend is dead…
OMG, Topher is DEAD.
I’m shaking so hard right now, Brendan.
I can’t stop crying.
Topher--he was my oldest friend. He knew everything about me.
Let’s put this in perspective, Luce.
Who knows how this even happened tonight
For all we know, Topher could have caused everything.
Brendan, that’s definitely not the right response right now.
You always hated him, didn’t you?
Is it because he was a guy and I was living with him?
Or is it because he “took me away from you” to live in Detroit?
Luce, stop.
You’re going to regret what you’re saying
Don’t tell me to stop, Brendan
You’re probably happy he’s dead
Now I know you didn’t mean THAT.
It’s probably just your grief talking.
Ugh. I’m sorry ☹
I’m sorry too
I shouldn’t have blamed him like that
Brendan, what am I going to do?
I want to go home
I want to go back to you
Maybe this art dream isn’t worth it
I knew you’d come around eventually… KIDDING.
That’s not funny.
Just trying to make you laugh
That’s supportive in a way, right?
Yeah, but it’s not the kind of support I need right now
I need to know what happened to Topher.
Shit, what if I’m still in danger?!
God, Brendan--I’m getting scared.
I just asked the policeman what happened…
And he didn’t answer me again.
That is really weird.
Isn’t he supposed to be there for you?
Yeah, it’s giving me a bad feeling…
I tried asking him louder.
But he still didn’t say anything.
I don’t like this…
OH MY GOD!!
He’s driving away.
He didn’t say anything and now he’s driving away
I’m freaking out
This doesn’t feel right…
Dammit, of course it doesn’t. This is so messed up…
Shit, Brendan!
I swear the car is speeding up
What the hell do you want me to do, Luce?
I don’t know
Should I tell you that I’m freaking out too?
Because I am, okay?
Look, I’m trying to be “supportive.”
But I don’t know what that looks like when you live there and I live here.
I’m sorry, I’m just so scared
It’s okay, I’m here.
Let me think.
2 minutes later
Start by asking the cop if you’re going to the police station.
That way it’s a simple yes or no answer.
Maybe he’ll give it to you.
Okay.
OMG. He said no.
OMG OMG. What do I do?
SHIT!
How fast is the car going?
Idk, like 30 mph?
Okay. Unlock the back door, open it, and tuck and roll
Brendan!
I know it’s scary and you could get hurt
But you have to get out of there.
No--that’s not why I’m freaking out.
I’m in the backseat of a cop car, Brendan
There aren’t any latches back here
Okay, okay. There’s got to be another way.
3 minutes later
Okay, hear me out
Besides your cellphone, do you have anything heavy and durable with you?
What does that even mean?!
What if you broke the window?
With what?
Exactly, Luce
Do you have something on you that’s strong enough to break the window?
I don’t think so
I have my cell, but I don’t have anything else
I left my apartment wearing pajamas
And I’m barefoot--no shoes.
Shit!
It’s okay
I’ll think of something
Thank you
Dammit, I’m scared
If I die tonight, know that I love you.
Luce, shut up
I love you too,  but shut up
You’re getting out of this alive
And coming home to me
I’ll support your artistic career here, and we’ll build a life together.
I love you, Brendan
I’m crying right now
I just want to get home to you.
You will--I have an idea
It’s not a great one, but it’s something
What if you smash the window with your elbow?
My elbow?
Brendan, the glass could cut a vein in my arms
I could bleed out and die!
But babe, I think you’re in serious danger with this “cop.”
It’s really weird that he’s driving away so quickly…
And that he won’t tell you where he’s going.
Cops don’t act sketchy like that.
You gotta try anything you can to get out
Okay
Wait. I’m gonna use my cell instead
I’ll lose you for now, but it’ll be safer
Idk, I don’t like not knowing where you are…
Not knowing how to help you.
Brendan, it’s less dangerous
Hold on--the cop picked up his phone
All he said was, “Okay boss.”
What do you think that means?
6 minutes later
Brendan?
OMG, Brendan, where are you?
Sorry, bathroom.
He said, “Ok boss”?
Yeah
WHAT THE HELL!
We’re pulling into the parking lot for an abandoned warehouse
Luce?
Were you going to say something?
3 minutes later
Lucy please answer me.
Or drop a pin so I know where you are.
10 minutes later
Brendan! Sorry
I’m here and alive
They threw me in some kind of prison cell
I had to tuck my phone in my bra so they didn’t see it
This is the one time I think I’ll say this, but…
Thank goodness you’re wearing a bra, huh?
Haha, stop
How can you be thinking about that right now?!
Haha, it made you smile, didn’t it?
Yeah, it did.😊
Good, sounds like I was being a supportive boyfriend then.
Let’s not push it 😉
Haha, okay. Let’s get you out of there
Describe your surroundings
Ok, James Bond
Luce?
Hi Lucy Jane McMillan. This is your roommate, Christopher Adam Slouth.
I go by Topher.
We’ve been living together in Detroit, MI for 5 months and have been studying at the Kresge art fellowship.
I don’t know where I am and this isn’t my cellphone, but I need your help.
Please don’t text anyone else. Just listen to me.
